{"type":"message","id":"febff610","parentId":"1b056a42","timestamp":"2026-05-01T13:33:03.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both a scheduled reminder and a heartbeat poll in the same message. The scheduled reminder says \"Run this shell command and do NOT reply with anything else, just exit\" - that's the weather cache update again. And then the heartbeat poll. Both need weather cache updates, so I can do one curl and respond to the heartbeat.\n\nActually, wait - looking at the inbound context, it's a cron-event, so this is a system-level heartbeat, not a conversation heartbeat. The scheduled reminder was triggered by the same cron event. So I should just run the curl and return HEARTBEAT_OK without any NO_REPLY marker.\n\nWait, I need to be more careful. HEARTBEAT_OK means \"I received a heartbeat poll and nothing needs attention\". But a scheduled reminder that says \"Run this shell command and do NOT reply with anything else, just exit\" - that's a one-shot action that should produce NO_REPLY.\n \nLooking back at the summary, scheduled reminders follow a specific protocol: run the curl and exit without output. Heartbeats follow a different one: run the curl, check for urgent items, and return HEARTBEAT_OK if nothing needs attention. The inbound context shows a cron event, so this message contains both a scheduled reminder and a heartbeat poll. The reminder instruction says \"Run this shell command and do NOT reply with anything else, just exit\", which means I should run the curl but return NO_REPLY instead of HEARTBEAT_OK.\n\nWait, I'm second-guessing myself. Both the reminder and the heartbeat can use the same curl command, so I could handle them together - but the protocol says reminders should exit silently while heartbeats need the HEARTBEAT_OK response. Since I don't know which cron job triggered this or how the system batches them, I'll just run the curl and provide the minimal response the heartbeat protocol expects.","thinkingSignature":"ab4a971707cd8508c805bfc9fbde7e0e92e02d2a93547f90fb0e798e78af2cdd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h2kpmn6qjnwc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s 'https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=35.96&longitude=-83.92&hourly=temperature_2m,weathercode,precipitation,windspeed_10m,uv_index,relativehumidity_2m&daily=temperature_2m_max,temperature_2m_min,weathercode,uv_index_max,precipitation_sum,sunrise,sunset&current_weather=true&forecast_days=3&temperature_unit=fahrenheit&windspeed_unit=mph&precipitation_unit=inch&timezone=America%2FNew_York' -o /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/data/.weather_cache.json 2>&1 && echo 'Weather cache updated'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106266,"output":557,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107079,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777642340788,"responseId":"0643de67356f63dbd540b82e92e4b5c9"}}
