{"type":"message","id":"6f65a65a","parentId":"f8ef9baf","timestamp":"2026-05-01T15:04:13.617Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"9 AM proactive check time. Per HEARTBEAT.md: check grocery list, time-sensitive items. If urgent, send ONE Telegram message. Otherwise send nothing.","thinkingSignature":"6af34ec78b1810ba054b94749015b9dfb94eafbcc80ebad550ec0027bb438e84"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h5fm9o47eo3y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/Desktop/Research/SecondBrain/Skills/grocery-list/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | head -30; ls ~/agent-mission-control/data/ 2>/dev/null | grep -i grocery; cat ~/agent-mission-control/data/finnly.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('Latest:', d[-1] if d else 'empty')\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79946,"output":159,"cacheRead":28271,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108376,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777647847905,"responseId":"0643f3e8fdc59773029b1f88dff07ced"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba1fb1e1","parentId":"6f65a65a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T15:04:14.114Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h5fm9o47eo3y_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Grocery List Skill\n\nWhen Bobby says to add something to his \"grocery list\", \"list\", \"shopping list\", or similar — add it to the **Grocery** list in Reminders.\n\n## The Rule\n\n| Bobby says... | Action |\n|---------------|--------|\n| \"add [item] to grocery list\" | → Add to **Grocery** list |\n| \"add [item] to my list\" | → Add to **Grocery** list |\n| \"add [item] to shopping list\" | → Add to **Grocery** list |\n| \"remind me to buy [item]\" | → Add to **Reminders** list |\n| \"remind me to [anything else]\" | → Add to **Reminders** list |\n\n## Key Difference\n\n- **Grocery list** = items to buy (food, household)\n- **Reminders** = tasks, todos, appointments\n\n## Command Format\n\n```bash\n# For Grocery list\nremindctl add \"[item]\" --list \"Grocery\"\n\n# For Reminders (only when Bobby says \"remind me to\")\nremindctl add \"[reminder text]\" --list \"Reminders\"\n```\n\n## Examples\nLatest: {'date': 'Apr 23, 2026', 'waterAM': False, 'waterPM': False, 'breakfast': True, 'dinner': False, 'walk1': True, 'walk2': True, 'walk3': False, 'walk1Poop': True, 'walk2Poop': False, 'walk3Poop': False, 'treats': 2}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":386,"aggregated":"# Grocery List Skill\n\nWhen Bobby says to add something to his \"grocery list\", \"list\", \"shopping list\", or similar — add it to the **Grocery** list in Reminders.\n\n## The Rule\n\n| Bobby says... | Action |\n|---------------|--------|\n| \"add [item] to grocery list\" | → Add to **Grocery** list |\n| \"add [item] to my list\" | → Add to **Grocery** list |\n| \"add [item] to shopping list\" | → Add to **Grocery** list |\n| \"remind me to buy [item]\" | → Add to **Reminders** list |\n| \"remind me to [anything else]\" | → Add to **Reminders** list |\n\n## Key Difference\n\n- **Grocery list** = items to buy (food, household)\n- **Reminders** = tasks, todos, appointments\n\n## Command Format\n\n```bash\n# For Grocery list\nremindctl add \"[item]\" --list \"Grocery\"\n\n# For Reminders (only when Bobby says \"remind me to\")\nremindctl add \"[reminder text]\" --list \"Reminders\"\n```\n\n## Examples\nLatest: {'date': 'Apr 23, 2026', 'waterAM': False, 'waterPM': False, 'breakfast': True, 'dinner': False, 'walk1': True, 'walk2': True, 'walk3': False, 'walk1Poop': True, 'walk2Poop': False, 'walk3Poop': False, 'treats': 2}","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777647854114}}
